    <title>Arctic contributor: Ross A. Virginia and Michael Sfraga</title>
    <description>Ross Virginia is the Myers Family professor of environmental science in the Environmental Studies Program and director of the Institute of Arctic Studies at Dartmouth College in Hanover, NH. He is co-lead scholar of the Fulbright Arctic Initiative and co-director of the University of the Arctic Institute for Arctic Policy.
Mike Sfraga is vice chancellor for University and Student Advancement and professor of Arctic policy in the School of Natural Resources and Extension at the University of Alaska Fairbanks. He is co-lead scholar of the Fulbright Arctic Initiative and co-director of the University of the Arctic Institute for Arctic Policy.
</description>
